        "created_at": "2018-11-19T22:03:24.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"147421\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>If memory serves me correctly I had the JL over the summer and it was in desperate need of air. A ton of VA upfront that was tough to get past but when it finally blew off and opened up it was singing. I\u2019d give it 2-3 hours of air if your bottle shows the same as mine did on the PnP. Love me some Kalin!</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Excuse my ignorance but VA as in volatile acidity?  Thanks for the advice regarding air time.</p>",
