      {
        "id": 2525928,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-11-20T10:21:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The 1980 Kalin Cuv\u00e9e JL is a very rare bottle, where did you find it? Current release is 1999\u2026 1980 JL is a great wine and I have never encountered any VA, one of the best Kalin Pinot Noirs I have tasted in fact. The last bottle I had, I decanted and served which only did the wine good.</p>",
