      {
        "id": 2526662,
        "name": "John Gilman",
        "username": "John_Gilman",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/67e7ee/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-11-21T17:13:23.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The 1980 Kalin Cuvee JL was drinking beautifully the last time I had it and was probably still good until 2030, so I do not think you need to worry too much about its fragility- there is still even a bit of tannin. Give it a good thirty minutes in decanter before serving to let it really blossom (or taste it after you decant it and see what you think). Emphatically do not serve it straight from the bottle, as there is plenty of sediment and Terry and Frances\u2019 pinots really need air to blososm- even when they are respectable old gentlemen like the 1980. The fruit is from Dutton Ranch.</p>\n<p>Have not had the 1980 Chalone in a month of Mondays, but would expect it also to be extant and drinking pretty well. But, I have not tasted it for a long, long time, so have no idea where it is now. I would again decant it before serving.</p>",
