      {
        "id": 2527029,
        "name": "Eric Lundblad",
        "username": "Eric_Lundblad",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/cdc98d/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-11-22T07:54:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had the 80 Chalone ~5 or so years ago, from a magnum. It was quite good and surprisingly youthful for a wine that age. Rose hips, cranberries and other bright red fruits, stems and other appealing herbal nuances, with a firm but not dominating structure. Based on other Chalone\u2019s I\u2019ve had from the same era, I\u2019d expect 750\u2019s to drink as well, or similarly, as this mag did.</p>",
